{"title": "Unsanitized user input in HTTP request (SSRF)", "summary": " Using unsanitized URLs from the request object when retrieving data puts your application at risk of server-side request forgery (SSRF) attacks. This rule checks for URLs containing user-supplied data. ", "description": "\nUsing unsanitized URLs from the request object when retrieving data puts your application at risk of server-side request forgery (SSRF) attacks.\nThis rule checks for URLs containing user-supplied data.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid using user input in URLs:\n\n```javascript\naxios.get(`https://${req.params.host}`)\n```\n\n\u2705 Use user input indirectly to form a URL:\n\n```javascript\nvar host = \"default-api.com\"\nif req.params.host == \"something-else\" {\n  host = \"other-api.com\"\n}\n\naxios.get(`https://${host}`)\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-918"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/javascript_express_server_side_request_forgery", "https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Server_Side_Request_Forgery_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}